Caesar demands that the Germans leave Gaul, but they say that they cannot endure the Suebi. He then proposes that they settle among the Ubii, just on the other side of the Rhine. The Germans ask that Caesar remain where he is while this proposal is being considered, but Caesar thinks this is a ruse to gain time.
